Okay, the user wants blunt, opinionated, Gen Z-style feedback. Keep it short and impactful! No sugarcoating. We can mention the text of the message, but avoid identifying the person from the screenshot—just say &quot;the sender.&quot;

Maybe suggest: &quot;Mute for tonight, don&#x27;t hit reply.” Get some distance before responding. Don’t rush. Sometimes using &quot;Do not reply tonight&quot; is a good tactic (night courage vibes!).

I&#x27;ll also make sure to stay away from quoting too much—paraphrasing keeps things tight! I&#x27;ll give them what they need without over-complicating it.
